						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Two faces of a rectangular stone, standing in front of the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Trailōkyamalla (Sōmēśvara I)—A.D. 1057.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [9]79, [Hēma] lambi, Chaitra, puṇṇame, Sunday, lunar eclipse and Mēsha-saṁkrānti</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1057, March 23.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of land and money by Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Bijjarasa,</hi> described as ‘Lord of Kālañjarapura’, to a temple (name lost). Also records a gift of land probably to the same temple by Dharmaśiva-Bhaṭāra.</p>						

						</summary>
